			<ns0:name>cbiffle@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/cbiffle@google.com/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Bennet has noticed a number of paths in the sel_ldr that disable sandbox features (like the validator) in response to environment variables.  Someone needs to go through these and consider them very carefully: exposing our security to possible environment pollution seems imprudent.

These options should be conditionally compiled out using the DANGEROUS flag.  If this isn't possible we need a very clear justification.

